divs: Sighting DetailsAt first, it seemed like a faint pink cloud, like a plane trail. As I drove down 15 toward Lewisburg, my passenger and I noticed that it consisted of pinkish orange lights, about eight, with one unlit moving back and forth across. This was not a plane or a tower. It hovered diagonally over the side of one of the mountain tops.
Summary: Lights pulsating, pinkish orange. Seemed to be hovering diagonally over mountain top.
